title: Indonesia Unemployment Rate
description: Unemployment Rate in Indonesia increased to 5.34 percent in the third quarter of 2018 from 5.13 percent in the first quarter of 2018. Unemployment Rate in Indonesia averaged 6.05 percent from 1982 until 2018, reaching an all time high of 11.24 percent in the third quarter of 2005 and a record low of 2 percent in the fourth quarter of 1983. In Indonesia, the unemployment rate measures the number of people actively looking for a job as a percentage of the labour force. This page provides the latest reported value for - Indonesia Unemployment Rate - plus previous releases, historical high and low, short-term forecast and long-term prediction, economic calendar, survey consensus and news.
author: Statistics Indonesia
